Placa Nova



In front of the Cathedral. The letters say "Barcino", the ancient name for the city,
which supposedly was named by the Carthaginians after Hannibal's father, Hamil Barca.
Taken Sunday, September 09, 2001, 11:06:16am.  Original image size: 1200x1600, 1.0Mb
Technical details: Olympus C700UZ, 1/50s @ F7.0, ISO 100, 94mm
